<tbody>
<tr>
<td><strong>Emerald Hill</strong></td>
<td>Sonic 2</td>
<td>Open green fields and cascading waterfalls. The introductory zone eases you into 3D movement with gentle terrain and forgiving layout</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Angel Island</strong></td>
<td>Sonic 3&amp;K</td>
<td>Starts on a tropical beach, then the forest catches fire between acts — faithfully recreating the iconic moment from Sonic 3. Wide branching paths reward exploration</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Ice Cap</strong></td>
<td>Sonic 3&amp;K</td>
<td>Visually the most stunning zone. Expansive snowy landscapes with sliding mechanics. The penguin enemies are relentless — they will chase you down and land hits</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Mystic Cave</strong></td>
<td>Sonic 2</td>
<td>Dark underground caverns with floor arrows for orientation. Act 2 has a vertical climbing section that punishes mistakes — miss one jump and you repeat the whole ascent</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Aqua Lake</strong></td>
<td>Sonic 2 (MS)</td>
<td>A deep cut from the Master System game, never before seen in 3D. Colorful waterslide sections and a laid-back pace make this the most relaxing zone</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><strong>Oil Ocean</strong></td>
<td>Sonic 2</td>
<td>The final and hardest zone. Industrial hazards everywhere, leading to a multi-phase octopus boss. Improved lighting in the Final Build gives it much better atmosphere</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

